INSERT INTO `jos_zoo_search_index` VALUES (2,'aaa724a9-b7e8-4982-b8cf-049e95da2bf6','Intern'),(2,'6627af16-de5e-44c6-9be3-ebd7a104f8b8','Social Media'),(2,'ef1f3d1b-7c73-47f1-b9cc-27809ea8705c','kylebohac'),(3,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Anna Melvin'),(3,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Oct 30'),(3,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','5:00-6:30pm'),(3,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','6 weeks'),(3,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(3,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$30'),(3,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(3,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(3,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','Week 1- \"Islam Rising\" Week 2- \"Belief & Ritual\" Week 3- \"Attitude of an Ambassador\" Week 4- \"Bridging the Gospel\" Week 5- \"Understanding the New Testament\'s Credibility\" Week 6- \"Understanding Jesus\' Sacrifice\"\r\n* Class fee includes materials.'),(4,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Lawson Flowers, Tyler David'),(4,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','This class exists to teach young college men how God has designed, redeemed and called all men to be the servant- leaders of their family, local church and society.\r\nWeek 1 Religion vs. Irreligion  Week 2 How Men Destroyed the World  Week 3 True Masculinity  Week 4 Making Disciples  Week 5 Missional Community  Week 6 Making War on Sin  Week 7 The Call to Lead'),(4,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(4,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(4,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 6'),(4,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','5:00-6:45pm'),(4,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','7 weeks'),(4,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(5,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','St. John Campus'),(5,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','we'),(5,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 28-Nov 16'),(5,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','7:00-8:30 PM'),(5,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','8 weeks'),(5,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(5,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$30'),(5,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Todd Engstrom'),(5,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','This on-ramp class is designed for people who desire to get connected into community at The Austin Stone. We will be studying the Gospel Centered Life curriculum together. This curriculum is challenging and beneficial for everyone, regardless of where you are in your walk with Christ. Group connection and discussion is an integral part of this class, as we develop deeper community through study and activities outside of class. Groups will be led by trained missional community leaders and you will have the opportunity to continue as an inter-generational missional community after the class is over. Class fee includes any childcare needs and course materials.'),(6,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','St. John Campus'),(6,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(6,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 20'),(6,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','11:00am-12:30pm'),(6,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','9 weeks'),(6,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','2-3 Hours of Homework per Week'),(6,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(6,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Troy & Kara Alexander, Jake Baskin'),(6,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','This is a combined course that is jointly held with the Crossing Cultures class each week. It has an added Saturday training specifically geared for formal volunteers with Refugee Services of Texas. However before we can engage refugees directly it is essential we seek to understand how to appropriately engage with a different cultures in a Christ-like manner. We will examine culture and its impact on relationships and explore how God wants us to respond to a multicultural world. In this course, we will process how our culture affects our behavior, beliefs and even our understanding of what it means to be a follower of Jesus. You will participate in hands-on experiences with Refugees and will be assisted in identifying barriers and bridges to building relationships cross-culturally.\r\nThis course requires the books Crossing Cultures and Who is my Neighbor?'),(7,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(7,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(7,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 6'),(7,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','7:00-8:30pm'),(7,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','7 weeks'),(7,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(7,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$30'),(7,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Fabienne Harford'),(7,'3f4be974-e0c5-4256-887f-c4f3ffd353a6','Women'),(7,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','As Christians, we should wrestle to understand the deep things of our faith and share all that God has revealed about Himself and His promises. Join us as we reflect on all that God has done for us in the gospel and give reason for the hope that is in us by digging into big questions like: How can a loving God send people to Hell? How could a good God allow suffering?\r\nWeek 1: Intro\r\nWeek 2: How can we trust the Bible?\r\nWeek 3: Redefining the Gospel\r\nWeek 4: How could a loving God send people to Hell?\r\nWeek 5: How could a good God ordain suffering?\r\nWeek 6: Mighty to Save: God\'s plan for salvation\r\nWeek 7: Q&A\r\n*Class fee includes bound and published curriculum'),(100,'ea1a9fd7-6fdf-482b-9022-48d877e2a717','43:07'),(8,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','St. John Campus'),(8,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(8,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 20'),(8,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','9:00-11:15am'),(8,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','9 weeks'),(8,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','2-3 Hours of Homework per Week'),(8,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(8,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Arrow Child and Family'),(8,'3f4be974-e0c5-4256-887f-c4f3ffd353a6','Must be at least 21 years of age'),(8,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','The Austin Stone is partnering with Arrow Child & Family Ministries to host their foster and adoption training at the Austin Stone. This training will certify families, singles or couples to provide respite care for foster families, to become foster parents, and to adopt from the foster care system. It is not necessary to know in advance which particular opportunity families will be pursuing. Training will cover such topics as: communication, abuse/neglect, child development, and grief and loss. If you are unsure if this class is right for you, please feel free to attend the first week of class as an informational orientation session. You can then decide if this course is a good fit for your current situation.'),(36,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','St. John'),(36,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(36,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 6'),(36,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','7:00-8:30pm'),(36,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','9 weeks'),(10,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(10,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(10,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 6'),(10,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','9:00-10:45am'),(10,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','7 weeks'),(10,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(10,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$30'),(10,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Various teachers'),(10,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','The fact that God finds His ultimate satisfaction in Himself and not in us is the greatest news in all the world. This truth has tremendous implications to our understanding of the gospel and missions. This class will study how the nature of God’s happiness is designed for our ultimate joy and compels us to take His Name to the nations.  Week 1: Intro  Week 2: The Source of God\'s Joy Week 3: The Source of Our Joy Week 4: What is the Gospel Week 5: Battling Unbelief through Faith Week 6: The Purpose of Missions Week 7: Gospel Proclamation through Word and Deed  *Class fee includes bound & published participant guide.'),(11,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(11,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(11,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 20'),(11,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','9:00-10:45am'),(11,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','9 weeks'),(11,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','5+ hours of homework per week'),(11,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(11,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Fabienne Harford'),(11,'3f4be974-e0c5-4256-887f-c4f3ffd353a6','Women'),(11,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','Have you ever wandered how you can hear from God?  Are you eager to have two-way conversations with Him? Join us as we learn how to go deeper into the Word of God.  God has called us to know Him.  Growing in your ability to hear from Him through digging into His Word will transform your relationship with Him and your relationships with others.  This is an intensive lab-style class, and it will require a considerable amount of time outside of class.'),(12,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(12,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(12,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 13'),(12,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','5:00-6:45pm'),(12,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','7 weeks'),(12,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(12,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(12,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Val Vance, Jason Kovacs'),(12,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','One of the most important things that informs the way that we counsel ourselves and others is what we believe about God.  We have been given the gift of the Word so that we can better know God and have a lens through which to see the rest of life and all its circumstances.  This class will walk through various topics within the Bible including creation, the fall of man, the gospel, future grace, suffering and community to understand how each of these matters and affects our everyday life.  There is no pre-requisite for this class and it is the entry point for anyone that desires to serve within the Gospel Counseling ministry.   '),(13,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','St. John Campus'),(13,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(13,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 13'),(13,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','11:00am-12:30pm'),(13,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','8 weeks'),(13,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(13,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(13,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Kathleen Choe, Jason Kovacs'),(13,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','This course will address how God uses us as His instruments of change in the life of others. We will look specifically at how the gospel addresses such issues as anxiety, depression, addictions, lust, and anger. Learners will begin to interact with case studies and be given practical tools to be used in caring for others.   Gospel Counseling I is required.'),(14,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(14,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(14,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 6'),(14,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','11:00am-12:30pm'),(14,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','7 weeks'),(14,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 hours of homework per week + missional community'),(14,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(14,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Amanda Brown, Theresa King'),(14,'3f4be974-e0c5-4256-887f-c4f3ffd353a6','Women'),(14,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','The end goal of Identify is that women will fall more in love with Jesus, trusting in what God says in His Word, and obeying Him completely. This class is a Get Connected class, designed to connect women who are not currently in a missional community with a community that will continue after the semester is over. Women will meet once a week on a Wednesday night in addition to class time on Sunday.   Week 1: Introduction  Week 2: Clothed with the Identity of Christ Week 3: Children of God Week 4: Ambassadors of Christ Week 5: Foundations of Biblical Womanhood Week 6: Purity Week 7: Panel'),(15,'6055f16b-c2d8-4f28-bad2-9e121e3d1a82','\"Being new in town, we were able to connect with other Christian couples and make new friends.\"   \"It made me more aware of the dynamics of our marriage and has definitely given us things to think about for the future in dealing with the changes we have coming.\"'),(15,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(15,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(15,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 20'),(15,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','9:00-10:45am'),(15,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','9 weeks'),(15,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 hours of homework per week + missional community'),(15,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$45 per couple'),(15,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Jon & Amelia Dansby, Dave & Suzanne Barrett'),(15,'3f4be974-e0c5-4256-887f-c4f3ffd353a6','Married Couples'),(15,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','This class is designed to help you get connected to biblical community at The Austin Stone while examining the real issues of marriage and life through the lens of the gospel. Together, we’ll build a foundation on what the Bible teaches about God’s design for our marriages, and then explore issues like communication, finance, and conflict. Course commitment includes weekly participation in groups outside of class on Wednesday evenings. This class is designed primarily for those who are not already in a missional community.  ONLY ONE PERSON FROM EACH COUPLE NEEDS TO REGISTER.   Week 1 - Marriage and Community Week 2 - Purposes of Marriage Week 3 - Our roles within marriage Week 4 - Love and the Gospel Week 5 - Communication and your design Week 6 - The roots of conflict Week 7 - Finances Week 8 - Sex and the Glory of God Week 9 - What\'s next'),(16,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(16,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(16,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Oct 30'),(16,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','11:00am-12:30pm'),(16,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','6 weeks'),(16,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(16,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(16,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Tom Jordan'),(16,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','The purpose of this class is to equip and encourage business leaders to be on mission with their business practices and to honor God in all areas of their lives. How do you lead in business as a follower of Christ? How should the gospel impact the way you hire, pay employees, and seek profit for the company? This class will look at the gospel principles behind godly business practices and focus heavily on practical application.  Each semester the Missional Business class will include new material as well as on-going content.  Please feel free to re-visit the class, even if you have taken it before.'),(17,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(17,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(17,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 13'),(17,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','11:00am-12:30pm'),(17,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','8 weeks'),(17,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-3 hours of Homework per Week + missional community'),(17,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$45 per couple'),(17,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Lauren & Tyler David, Morgan & Jon Norris, Brian & Karen Riley'),(17,'3f4be974-e0c5-4256-887f-c4f3ffd353a6','Engaged couples and those who have been married 0-3 years'),(17,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','Spend time with others in this important life stage and learn principles of a Godly marriage, while discussing practical issues that we face when two become one. This class is meant to connect couples to a missional community, and participants will be required to participate in a mid-week missional community during the class (you\'ll be able to select a night(s) that work with your schedule when you sign up. If you\'re already in a missional community, we suggest temporarily leaving your existing group for this class. Please consider taking the class after you have completed Pre-Marital counseling. ONLY ONE PERSON FROM EACH COUPLE NEEDS TO REGISTER.  Week 1 - Intro/Get to know you Week 2 - Biblical Foundations of Marriage Week 3 - Needs/Roles/Responsibilities Week 4 - Conflict Resolution Week 5 - Communication Leading to Full Disclosure Week 6 - Finances and In Laws Week 7 - Sex and Sexuality Week 8 - Q&A Panel'),(17,'6055f16b-c2d8-4f28-bad2-9e121e3d1a82','\"1) The class encouraged my wife and me to engage in fruitful discussions, 2) The class provided a venue for making friends in the same life stage, who we now live missionally alongside, 3) The class informed us about marriage and how Scripture defines and guides this relationship.\"   \"This class has given us a great group of fellow believers and new friends to love and to be on mission with.  It has given us great understanding and wisdom to apply to our marriage to glorify God in it.\"   \"It has better prepared me for the reality of marriage.\"'),(18,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(18,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(18,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 20'),(18,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','11:00am-12:30pm'),(18,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','9 weeks'),(18,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(18,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(18,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','James Paquette, Halim Suh, Ryan King'),(18,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','Roughly 76% of the Bible is the Old Testament and there are over 2700 allusions to the OT from the NT.  What we see is that the OT gives the background for why we all desperately needed Jesus and why He is the only way a man can be saved.  So if we are to appreciate Christ’s work, purpose, message, His language, His terms, and His concepts as he spoke and taught, what we realize is that we critically need the OT. This class is ‘The Beginning’ of the journey through the OT as we cover at a survey level the first five books of the Bible.  Week 1: Introduction Week 2: Genesis - Creation, Rest, & Yahweh/Elohim Week 3: Genesis - The Fall Man & The Rise of Sin Week 4: Genesis - Abraham, Jacob & Joseph  Week 5: Exodus - Growth & Deliverance of God\'s People Week 6: Exodus - Covenant, Law, & the Tabernacle Week 7 :Leviticus - The Purpose of the Law Week 8: Numbers - The Land of Canaan Week 9: Deuteronomy - The New Covenant & Wrap-up'),(19,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(19,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(19,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 20'),(19,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','7:00-8:30pm'),(19,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','9 weeks'),(19,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(19,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(19,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','James Paquette, Halim Suh, Ryan King'),(19,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','OT Survey II will cover the Historical Books of the Old Testament. 12 books starting from Joshua through Esther. We will see God’s enduring Goodness as He leads His people in possessing the promised land, His enduring Fatherhood as He disciplines them through their Captivity in foreign lands and His enduring Faithfulness as He restores them back into their own land.  In the future semesters OT Survey 3 will cover the Poetic books: Job, Psalms, Proverbs, Ecclesiastes & Song of Solomon  And OT Survey 4 will cover the 17 Prophetic books: Major Prophets – Isaiah, Jereimiah, Lamentations, Ezekiel, Daniel Minor Prophets – Hosea, Joel, Amos, Obadiah, Jonah, Micah, Nahum, Habakkuk, Zephaniah, Haggai, Zechariah, Malachi'),(20,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(20,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(20,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Oct 30'),(20,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','5:00-6:45pm'),(20,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','6 weeks'),(20,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','1-2 Hours of Homework per Week'),(20,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(20,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Travis Wussow'),(20,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','What is the gospel? Why does God allow suffering in the world? How could a loving God send people to hell? How can one religion claim to be \'the only way\'? The Inconvenient God will walk through these basic questions of belief and the overarching story that the Bible tells. If you have questions or are exploring Christianity, this class is a great place to start. \r\n\r\nWeek 1: Intro Week 2: Is the Bible God’s Word? Week 3: The problem with hell Week 4: If God is good why is there suffering? Week 5: What is the gospel? Week 6: Q & A'),(20,'6055f16b-c2d8-4f28-bad2-9e121e3d1a82','\"I was on a slippery slope regarding my faith because I didn\'t fully understand why God allowed certain things to happen in my life so it was hard for me to trust Him.  Now that I know what God\'s purpose and mission is through us, it is so much easier for me to obediently follow without thinking why am I doing this.\"   \"I feel like before this class I was very dead inside.  I didn\'t have a heart for Jesus.  I didn\'t seek His influence in my life nor did I see it.  I had a lot of problems with scripture that were creating am emotional barrier in my relationship with Jesus.  More than anything I wanted to get over these problems but I couldn\'t do it on my own.  Taking this class helped me discover things about God that struck fear, awe, and love into my heart  So many of the things we learned I had known previously on an intellectual level, and although Ronnie was a great teacher, it was purely God\'s influence that let me believe it in my heart.  He answered my prayer, and I am tremendously grateful that he provided this class as a means to do so.\"   \"It shakes you up.  My foundation, my footing, is more uncertain.  And I think that is a good thing.  Not easy.  But good.\"'),(21,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(21,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(21,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 13'),(21,'a4dbc779-3d4e-4e9d-a6fa-4ae80cf537bf','5:00-6:45pm'),(21,'601d851e-74e7-4483-88d1-645e168eab25','8 weeks'),(21,'89da3d28-8ad4-4e39-9291-9c6de3a3f7c9','2-3 Hours of Homework per Week'),(21,'8572e862-0093-4495-9015-1bb61ca27dfb','$20'),(21,'3a93ed1f-382b-4d84-98c0-5061af342d8b','Various teachers'),(21,'acd8f0c9-89f2-4a1d-a946-6e604d886f8a','We believe that the Word of God is living and active and that it is able to pierce deep and dissect every miniscule detail of our life.  What does the whole council of Scripture say about various theological topics? These are the things that we will be looking at together as we take Theology from the Head to the Heart and from the Heart to our Hands.'),(22,'23c51773-2821-4500-aff4-288d40077efd','Austin High Campus'),(22,'8ec757c9-819f-4a86-a2c6-e541173009a1','Su'),(22,'bbcdf21d-538c-44a6-a610-ae0d44231faa','Sep 25-Nov 6'),(2